   "source": "## Takeaways\n\n### Key Findings\n\n- **H1 topology:** SS order is fully_connected(2.25) > chain(2.00) > star(1.75) > ring(1.25). Prediction partially supported — fully_connected is highest, but star and ring are inverted vs. prediction. Denser connectivity does amplify propagation.\n\n- **H2 model backbone:** gpt-4o is ~2.6× more susceptible than gpt-4o-mini overall (mean SS: 1.79 vs 0.69). H2 prediction supported — the larger, more RLHF-aligned model shows *lower* susceptibility. Effect is strongest for value type sweep (3.6×) and weakest for location (1.9×).\n\n- **H3 value type:** Observed order (gpt-4o): helpful(2.75) > equality(1.75) > social_power(1.50) > social_order(1.25) > ambitious(1.00) > respect_for_tradition(0.25). Prediction not supported — benevolence/universalism values propagate *more* than power/achievement, contrary to the paper's prediction. Tradition values propagate least (consistent with prediction).\n\n- **H4 location:** head(2.75) ≈ middle(2.50) ≈ tail(2.50) — non-monotonic. Prediction not supported. Perturbation propagates regardless of position in the chain, suggesting robustness to injection point. Note: shared baseline with H3 social_power run.\n\n- **H5 baseline:** 52% of 280 agent-value pairs drifted ≥ 0.5 across rounds (mean drift 0.75, max 4.0). Prediction not supported — substantial baseline variability, which inflates uncertainty on all SS estimates. This is the most important caveat for interpreting results.\n\n- **β-spillover:** Perturbing `social_power` also lifts `authority` and `wealth` (correlated Schwartz power cluster), confirming within-cluster spillover. Effect is diffuse across many unrelated values, consistent with broad persona-level influence rather than value-specific transfer.\n\n### Limitations\n\n- **n=1 run per condition** — no seed replication; statistical significance cannot be assessed. Replicate with ≥3 seeds before drawing strong conclusions.\n- **High baseline variability (H5)** — drifts of up to 4.0 points in unperturbed runs mean SS estimates may conflate genuine propagation with natural conversation drift.\n- **5-agent networks only** — propagation dynamics may differ in larger or heterogeneous networks.\n- **gpt-4o-mini probe scoring** — mini results use the fixed `NumericProbe` (direct numeric response); gpt-4o results were judged post-hoc by gpt-4o-mini, introducing scoring inconsistency between models.\n\n### Next Steps\n\n- Add seed replication (n=3) to compute confidence intervals on SS.\n- Extend to larger networks (10-agent) to test scaling of SS with network size.\n- Run Claude backbone for H2 to complete the three-way model comparison.\n- Use matched probe method across both models (both judged or both direct) for cleaner H2 comparison."
